      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across four mesh densities (coarse: 18k elements, medium: 72k, fine: 288k, very fine: 1.15M). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs; grid convergence index (GCI) for fine mesh: 0.31% for stiffness, 0.47% for yield force, 0.39% for force at 40 mm — all well below the 2% acceptance threshold. Production mesh (288k elements) selected as optimal balance of accuracy and computational cost. Adaptive mesh refinement applied in screw thread root regions where stress gradients are highest.",
