      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary biomechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the regulatory decision regarding structural adequacy of the pedicle screw construct. Stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force determines the onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to catastrophic failure scenarios. All three QoIs are used in FDA 510(k) substantial equivalence comparisons.",
